23/01/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The president of Italy's Chamber of Deputies, Pierferdinando Casini, confirmed on Friday (21 January) that his country continues to back Albania's EU integration efforts.
During talks with Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano, he noted that Albania has an important role as a factor for regional stability.
Nano, in turn, urged Italian companies to invest in Albania.
Casini also held a meeting with President Alfred Moisiu, focusing on the need to develop economic co-operation between the two countries.
(ATA - 21/01/05)
